This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with machine translation, a subfield of natural language processing. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of embeddings, which is a common technique in both cs.CL and cs.LG. The paper may also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with automated translation, a task that falls under the umbrella of AI. The use of neural networks also falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper may be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it discusses the use of encoder-decoder networks, which are commonly used in image captioning tasks.
